{"title":"Metal from the North! Otso Cycles’ New Warakin Steel All-Road Bike is Ready For Action","link":"https://bikerumor.com/otso-cycles-new-warakin-steel-all-road-bike/","date":1721746800000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-hero.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" alt=\"(Photos / Otso Cycles)\" /></p>\n<p>Today, Minnesota’s <a href=\"https://otsocycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Otso Cycles</a> releases the new <a href=\"https://otsocycles.com/collections/warakin-steel-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">Warakin</a>, a steel all-road bike designed for multi-surface rides, overnighters, gravel races, commuting, or whatever you feel like throwing at it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-headtube-badge.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-headtube-badge.jpeg\" alt=\"Otso Cycles Steel Warakin headtube badge\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-headtube-badge.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-headtube-badge-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-headtube-badge-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-headtube-badge-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-headtube-badge-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-headtube-badge-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos / Otso Cycles)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Steel Warakin</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The steel Warakin shares the same frame geometry as its siblings, the Warakin <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/otso-warakin-stainless-ti-gravel-frames-get-updated-to-accommodate-more-cargo-suspension/\" target=\"_blank\">Stainless</a>, and Warakin <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-grx-1-x-12-dream-build-otso-warakin-ti-adventure-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">Ti</a> – now, it’s just available in 4130 chromoly as well. Frame features include adjustable geometry, a ton o’ mounts for cargo and fenders, the ability to run gears or as a single speed, plus clearance for 50mm tires. The geometry is also suspension-corrected, so you could run a suspension fork if that floats your boat.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-Downtube-logo.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-Downtube-logo.jpeg\" alt=\"Otso Cycles Steel Warakin Downtube logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-Downtube-logo.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-Downtube-logo-297x186.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-Downtube-logo-120x75.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-Downtube-logo-768x480.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The carbon, painted to match fork sports an axle-to-crown of 420mm. All of the above contributes to a progressive geometry that will comfortably and confidently carry the rider along the road ahead, no matter the terrain.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-in-the-woods.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-in-the-woods.jpeg\" alt=\"Otso Cycles Steel Warakin in the woods\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-in-the-woods.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-in-the-woods-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-in-the-woods-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-in-the-woods-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-in-the-woods-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-in-the-woods-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Coming in sizes 52, 54, 56, 58, and 60cm, the steel Warakin follows the same size-specific geo as the Warakin Stainless and Ti versions. The 49cm frame has been newly designed for shorter riders. It was developed with 650b wheels in mind. This reduces toe overlap, while still offering frame tire clearance of 50mm, the same number of cargo mounts, rear rack, and fenders. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-warakin-toptube.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-warakin-toptube.jpeg\" alt=\"Otso Cycles Steel Warakin warakin toptube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-warakin-toptube.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-warakin-toptube-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-warakin-toptube-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-warakin-toptube-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-warakin-toptube-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-warakin-toptube-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Otso Warakin is made from custom-butted 4130 chromoly tubing. The classic tubing and progressive geo provide a stable and smooth ride, making it ideal for light touring. The fork that comes stock on the Warakin is the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/hiili-carbon-gravel-fork-clears-the-biggest-tires-officially-launches-lithic-components/\" target=\"_blank\">Lithic Hiili carbon fork</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tire Clearance and Tuning Chip</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tire-clearace.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tire-clearace.jpeg\" alt=\"Otso Cycles Steel Warakin tire clearace\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tire-clearace.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tire-clearace-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tire-clearace-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tire-clearace-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tire-clearace-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tire-clearace-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If a drop bar bike is truly designed to ride on any road in any condition, it’s going to need ample tire clearance. The Warakin has a big tire clearance of 700c x 50mm. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tuning-chip-dropout.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tuning-chip-dropout.jpeg\" alt=\"Otso Cycles Steel Warakin tuning chip dropout\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tuning-chip-dropout.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tuning-chip-dropout-297x186.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tuning-chip-dropout-120x75.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tuning-chip-dropout-768x480.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like many other bikes in the Otso family, the Warakin runs a Tuning chip rear dropout system. This allows the rider to lengthen or shorten the wheelbase by up to 20mm. This can raise and lower the bottom bracket by 4mm as well as change the headtube angle by +/- 0.2 degrees. All of this can be done at a home workshop with a few tools.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Warakin Frame &amp; Fork Features</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-logo-and-bag.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-logo-and-bag.jpeg\" alt=\"Otso Cycles Steel Warakin logo and bag\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-logo-and-bag.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-logo-and-bag-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-logo-and-bag-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-logo-and-bag-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-logo-and-bag-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-logo-and-bag-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Even beyond the geometry, you’ll find the Warakin is versatile. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Bottle bosses on the seat tube, and triple mounts on the top and underside of the downtube</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bottle bosses/mounts on each fork leg</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rear rack compatible</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fits front and rear fenders</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Made for externally routed cables and housing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cable/housing outed under the downtube, and chainstays make room for bags and ease of service </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Retail and Colorways</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tangerine.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tangerine.jpeg\" alt=\"Otso Cycles Steel Warakin tangerine\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tangerine.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tangerine-297x186.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tangerine-120x75.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-tangerine-768x480.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Tangerine</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-racing-green.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-racing-green.jpeg\" alt=\"Otso Cycles Steel Warakin racing green\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-racing-green.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-racing-green-297x186.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-racing-green-120x75.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-racing-green-768x480.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Racing Green</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-nevy-gold.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-nevy-gold.jpeg\" alt=\"Otso Cycles Steel Warakin navy gold\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-nevy-gold.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-nevy-gold-297x186.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-nevy-gold-120x75.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Otso-Cycles-Steel-Warakin-nevy-gold-768x480.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Navy Gold</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can get the Warakin built to order via the Otso Custom Bike Builder. This allows customers to choose everything from drivetrain, wheel size, tires, handlebar width, stem length, and more. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $1400 (frame, fork, Tuning Chip hardware, axles, seatpost clamp, and bottle cage bolts)<br />Pricing for a complete bike built with Shimano GRX 11-speed starts at $2,500 or Shimano GRX 12-speed at $2,800.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Colors: Tangerine, Navy Gold, and Racing Green</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Warakin is available now at the link below, or at any bike shop that stocks Otso.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://otsocycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">OtsoCycles.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/otso-cycles-new-warakin-steel-all-road-bike/\">Metal from the North! Otso Cycles’ New Warakin Steel All-Road Bike is Ready For Action</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"faf3279d72563d72c6432f24f8916f14b26f99cd21fb1280a512b4ae0cdb5556","category":"Cycling"}